rComments: McCaffrey is probably the best instructor there. His courses are stressful but you wind up learning an incredible amount that you can put to use right away. He claims that you will be better than most gov doc librarians after you finish his course and he is right. If you want to learn practical things from a great prof. take his courses.

Really knowledgeable professor, but a lot of work. Better take this course when you have time to spend hours on research. And it is only worth a little if anything at the end for your professional career.
